                        FERC OPEN & SPECIAL MEETINGS FOR JANUARY 2002

          Meeting Dates, Times and Agenda are Subject to Change by FERC without Notice

If you are interested in FERC Open and Special Meetings throughout the year you may  want to consider a Yearly Internet Package which includes: Open and Special Meetings covered by the Capitol Connection and unlimited access to the Archives (available for 3 months).

                           SPECIAL MEETINGS FOR JANUARY 2002

The Capitol Connection is pleased to announce that it will broadcast (via the internet and telephone) the following Federal Energy Regulatory Commission Special Meetings:

Thursday, Jan. 17, 2002, 9 a.m. - 5 p.m. EST 
Topic:  Interconnection Project. 
This meeting is being held in the Commission Meeting Room in Washington, DC.   This meeting is available via the Internet and Phone Bridge only.
For Contract go to:  www.capitolconnection.org <http://www.capitolconnection.org/> and click on the FERC link on the sidebar and click on 'This Month's FERC meetings'


Friday, Jan. 18, 2002, 9 a.m. - 5 p.m. EST 
Topic:  Interconnection Project. 
This meeting is being held in the Commission Meeting Room in Washington, DC.   This meeting is available via the Internet and Phone Bridge only.
For Contract go to:  www.capitolconnection.org <http://www.capitolconnection.org/> and click on the FERC link on the sidebar and click on 'This Month's FERC meetings'

Tuesday, Jan. 22, 2002, approx. 9:30 a.m.  4:30 p.m. EST 
Topic:  RTO -  Market Designs & Operations
This meeting is being held in the Commission Meeting Room in Washington, DC.   This meeting is available via the Internet and Phone Bridge only.
For Contract go to:  www.capitolconnection.org <http://www.capitolconnection.org/> and click on the FERC link on the sidebar and click on 'This Month's FERC meetings'

Wednesday, Jan. 23, 2002, approx. 9:30 a.m.  4:30 p.m. EST 
Topic:  RTO -  Market Designs & Operations
This meeting is being held in the Commission Meeting Room in Washington, DC.   This meeting is available via the Internet and Phone Bridge only.
For Contract go to:  www.capitolconnection.org <http://www.capitolconnection.org/> and click on the FERC link on the sidebar and click on 'This Month's FERC meetings'

Thursday, Jan. 31, 2002, approx. 9:00 a.m.  4:00 p.m. EST 
Topic:  Energy Infrastructure
This meeting is being held in the Helmsley Park Lane Hotel in New York City.   This meeting is available in Audio Only via the Internet and Phone Bridge only.
For Contract go to:  www.capitolconnection.org <http://www.capitolconnection.org/> and click on the FERC link on the sidebar and click on 'This Month's FERC meetings'


                                       OPEN MEETINGS FOR JANUARY 2002

The Capitol Connection is pleased to announce that it will broadcast the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission Open Meetings on:

*Wednesday,  Jan. 16, 2002, 10:00 am ET      

*After the Open Meeting FERC has scheduled a 'closed' meeting which will not be broadcast.


Wednesday,  Jan. 30, 2002, 10:00 am ET

(Open Meetings are available via the Internet, Phone Bridge and the Capitol Connection's Washington DC area wireless cable system)

Meeting dates and times are subject to change without notice. For current information, you can go to our website at www.capitolconnection.org <http://www.capitolconnection.org/> for a link to the FERC's page (you may need to Refresh your browser for the most current information to appear)  or you can go to the FERC's web page at www.ferc.gov <http://www.ferc.gov/> The FERC Office of the Secretary can be reached at 202.208.0400.

If you have an annual subscription to the Capitol Connection internet service, these meetings are included in the annual fee.  Please contact us if you are interested in signing up for either of these meetings or want to get an annual subscription to our internet service.

The Capitol Connection offers FERC meetings live via the Internet, as well as via phone bridge, and satellite, please visit our website at www.capitolconnection.org <http://www.capitolconnection.org/> or send e-mail to capcon@gmu.edu for more information. If there is a meeting you are interested in receiving, please call 703-993-3100.

Sincerely,

David Reininger



